description._content: Description: The Church. Location: Tristan Da Cunha Date: 1927 Description: One of the newer houses in the west end of the settlement. The houses are enlarged as the family grows. Each young man now has to build his own house before getting married. Location: Tristan Da Cunha Date: 1927 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/777 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
